The mock boundary confirms the issue is test-only collection: router tests intentionally neutralize `server-only` but import `server.ts` for types/context without invoking a real Supabase client. I’m preserving strict production/development behavior while giving `NODE_ENV=test` inert defaults only when variables are truly absent; explicitly blank variables still fail, so the schema regression test remains non-vacuous. This keeps unit tests isolated without weakening real boot validation.
